
Tutorial: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-wordpress-with-docker-compose

Setup:
 - Modify nginx.conf to include the proper domain
 - Modify the certbot service definition to include the correct email and domain
 - Modify .env to include prefered mysql info
 - curl -sSLo nginx-conf/options-ssl-nginx.conf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/certbot/certbot/master/certbot-nginx/certbot_nginx/_internal/tls_configs/options-ssl-nginx.conf

Run: docker-compose up -d

Check status:
 - docker-compose ps
   If srvice is not 0 or up:
   - docker-compose logs service_name